                <h2>Conclusion: Lessons from the Water Memory Debate</h2>

                <p>For most scientists today, the water memory theory represents an example of how extraordinary claims can capture public imagination despite lacking scientific support. Water memory contradicts the scientific understanding of physical chemistry and is not accepted by the scientific community based on decades of failed replication attempts.</p>

